+config BAREMETAL_SUITE
+	bool "Boot directly into the out-of-tree bare-metal RV64 test suite"
+	depends on RISCV_S_MODE
+	help
+	  When enabled, the RISC-V reset path (reset.S) diverts after the
+	  M->S transition into the out-of-tree rv64gcv bare-metal test suite
+	  (its s_mode_entry/test_main), using the suite's own M-mode trap
+	  vector (_m_trap_vector), instead of starting the Zephyr kernel.
+	  This exists to run that test suite verbatim on QEMU virt. Leave
+	  disabled (default n) for normal Zephyr builds, which are unaffected.
+
+config RISCV_MMU
+	bool "RISC-V Sv39 MMU support"
+	depends on RISCV_S_MODE && 64BIT
+	select CPU_HAS_MMU
+	select MMU
+	help
+	  Enable Sv39 page-table memory management for RISC-V in Supervisor mode
+	  (the S-mode counterpart to PMP, which is M-mode only).
+
+	  The kernel builds Sv39 page tables at boot (mapping the kernel image and
+	  device MMIO, identity-mapped), turns on paging via satp, and provides
+	  arch_mem_map()/arch_mem_unmap() so the generic memory-management layer
+	  (k_mem_map(), etc.) works. The QEMU virt CPU is also given the "mmu=on"
+	  capability so satp is writable -- the same knob the bare-metal suite uses
+	  under CONFIG_BAREMETAL_SUITE.
+
+	  Default n; a separate, opt-in flag that leaves stock Zephyr builds and
+	  the bare-metal suite (CONFIG_BAREMETAL_SUITE) byte-for-byte untouched.
+
+config RISCV_MMU_NUM_TABLES
+	int "Number of Sv39 page tables in the static pool"
+	depends on RISCV_MMU
+	default 32
+	help
+	  Size of the statically-reserved page-table pool (each table is one 4 KB
+	  page). Page tables cannot come from the kernel heap: they are needed at
+	  early boot before the heap exists and from under the MMU spinlock. The
+	  boot mapping needs only a few; the rest cover runtime arch_mem_map().
+	  Increase if a build panics with the pool exhausted.
+
